==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inflict
<hw>In*flict"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Inflicted</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Inflicting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>inflictus</ets>, p.
p. of <ets>infligere</ets> to strike on, to inflict; pref.
<ets>in-</ets> in, on + <ets>fligere</ets> to strike. Cf.
<er>Flail</er>.]</ety> <def>To give, cause, or produce by striking, or
as if by striking; to apply forcibly; to lay or impose; to send; to
cause to bear, feel, or suffer; <as>as, to <ex>inflict</ex> blows; to
<ex>inflict</ex> a wound with a dagger; to <ex>inflict</ex> severe pain
by ingratitude; to <ex>inflict</ex> punishment on an offender; to
<ex>inflict</ex> the penalty of death on a criminal.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What heart could wish, what hand <qex>inflict</qex>, this dire
disgrace?</q> <rj><qau>Drygen.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The persecution and the pain⟦br⟧
That man <qex>inflicts</qex> on all inferior kinds.</q>
<rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inflicter</ent>⟦br⟧
